## How Has This Been Tested (if applicable)?

Refactoring the examples on this branch: https://github.com/shuttle-hq/examples/pull/26 All examples have been ran with `cargo run --bin cargo-shuttle` locally and all of them work. The ones with databases may fail on the first run, and then succeed on the second, but I believe this is an old bug.

I also upgraded some dependencies, not a lot, but I ran `make images` to make sure it doesn't make us hit the cyclic dependency bug.

This PR allows options passed to resources to be string interpolated. For example in this `local_uri` option, the password is being read from the `Secrets.toml` file

```rust
#[shuttle_service::main]
async fn main(
    #[shuttle_shared_db::Postgres(
        local_uri = "postgres://postgres:{secrets.password}@localhost:16695/postgres"
    )]
    pool: PgPool,
) -> shuttle_service::ShuttlePoem<impl poem::Endpoint> {
    ...
}
```

With #596, this closes #497
